RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAPPY UNION raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the two path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole, and dueled down the stretch to just hold the win. SORTARIA chased the leaders between horses early, began a bid from the four path racing around the bend, and gained ground steadily to the wire, narrowly missing. LUVISANAKI bobbled slightly leaving the gate, recovered to duel on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the turn and weakened in the final furlong. WICKLOW GAL dueled on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, battled from the three path around the turn and faded in the lane. FULL TIME STRUTIN raced at the back of the pack on the inside in the early going, came around the bend in the two path and made no bid. RED DELICIOUS tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and tired in the stretch. SUNSHINE GIRL raced at the back of the pack on the outside through the opening stages, continued around the turn in the three path and was empty from there. PER FGCC CASE #2023-009301 DATED, 03-24-2023, SORTARIA WAS DISQUALIFIED DUE TO A MEDICATION VIOLATION.

ALIZEE tracked the leader between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn, could not go with the winner in the lane and chased that rival home, the best of the rest. NINJA ABARRIO raced off the pace early, came around the turn in the two path and improved position mildly in the lane. TRUE ATKA brushed mildly with the horse to her outside at the start, stalked the pace setter up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the bend and weakened in the stretch. MAGICGIRL trailed the field up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and was never a threat. DANCIN DEE chased the leader on the inside in the early going, saved ground around the bend and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. BAM BAM WARRIOR raced in the four path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, came around the far bend in the three path and kept on to the wire, no match for the winner. SWIFT KID bumped with the horse to his outside at the break, raced off the pace through the opening half mile, began to move up while saving ground around the far turn and improved position mildly in the stretch, no threat to the winner. GRAND PLAYER raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the second bend in the four path and finished evenly. GRAND SIR saved ground early, raced off the pace between horses up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and made no bid. GIOVANE'S PROMISE raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch at the back of the pack on the outside, navigated the far turn still in the three path and was empty in the stretch. SMARTHUMOR hopped up slightly leaving the gate, raced in the four path around the first bend, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and tired in the lane.
